  "body": "### Version of Hardhat\r\n\r\n2.13.0\r\n\r\n### What happened?\r\n\r\n`changeTokenBalances` does not allow to track balances of multiple tokens from single transaction. The snippet in reproduction should fail on first assertion but instead both of them pass.\r\n\r\n### Minimal reproduction steps\r\n\r\n  ```javascript\r\n  it('track multiple changeTokenBalances', async function () {\r\n      const { dai } = await loadFixture(initContracts);\r\n      await expect(dai.transfer(addr1.address, ether('0.1')))\r\n          .to.changeTokenBalances(dai, [addr, addr1], [ether('-0.2'), ether('0.2')])\r\n          .to.changeTokenBalances(dai, [addr, addr1], [ether('-0.1'), ether('0.1')]);\r\n  });\r\n  ```\r\n  \r\n  ### Search terms\r\n\r\nchai-matchers",
